vulnerability.name: USN-6467-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6467-1 fixed a vulnerability in Kerberos. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS, Ubuntu 22.04 LTS and Ubuntu 23.04.  Original advisory details:   Robert Morris discovered that Kerberos did not properly handle memory  access when processing RPC data through kadmind, which could lead to the  freeing of uninitialized memory. An authenticated remote attacker could  possibly use this issue to cause kadmind to crash, resulting in a denial  of service.

statements.status_notes: Kerberos could be made to crash if it received specially crafted network traffic.
